track_notes: The path that starts from the village of Blavy (Roisan) is well traced and thanks to exposure to the southwest allows you to make pleasant excursions even in late autumn and early spring. The route is fairly long and in the final part of the ascent to the Colle di Viou (2.700 m.) It is also quite steep but the spectacle that can be enjoyed from the top repays the effort. At the top there is a metal cross with a stone base in which there is the box with the diary of the climber, the central position provides a panoramic view of the city of Aosta, Valpelline and the giants: Mont Blanc, Grandes- Jorasses, Matterhorn, Monte rosa, the Swiss Grand-Combin and other famous peaks such as Grivola and Emilius.

A breve distanza dalla cima ci sarebbe un bel bivacco dove passare la notte. la prossima volta. 
Bel panorama su tutta la valle . Operatività VHF solo locale.
